labels.en: Immersed Tunnel Ontology - Core Foundation Module

comments.en:
Core foundation module establishing fundamental base classes for immersed tunnel engineering ontology.
      Aligned with GBT 51318-2019 "Immersed Tunnel Design Standard" providing standardized semantic infrastructure.
      
      This module defines foundational concepts including:
      - Calculation stages corresponding to construction phases per GBT 51318-2019 methodology
      - Limit states for structural analysis and safety verification
      - Project deliverables and documentation framework
      - Base component classifications for tunnel elements
      
      STANDARDS ALIGNMENT:
      - Construction stages follow GBT 51318-2019 design methodology
      - Terminology consistent with Chinese national standard definitions
      - Structural analysis framework supporting limit state design approach

comment.en: Grouting pipe for construction joints with specifications and position.
Steel shear key component with width, height, length specifications and embedded bolts.
Push-out section with length and parameters.
Post-weld section with length and parameters.

Joining phase involving precise alignment and connection of tunnel elements as defined in GBT 51318-2019 Section 2.1.5. This stage encompasses joint pressing operations, watertight seal installation, and structural continuity establishment between adjacent elements.
Round steel waterstop for GINA system with tube dimensions and centerline positioning per HPDI specifications.
Steel-edged waterstop with specifications and centerline path on cross-section.

Installation phase involving controlled submersion of tunnel elements to predetermined underwater positions as defined in GBT 51318-2019 Section 2.1.4. This stage includes ballasting operations, depth control, and underwater positioning accuracy requirements.
Procedural documentation specifying construction methodologies, sequencing, and quality control measures for immersed tunnel implementation.
Primary waterstop system for joint waterproofing using natural rubber gaskets with clamping fixation methods.

Abstract base class representing discrete physical or functional elements within an immersed tunnel system according to GBT 51318-2019 design framework. Provides foundational semantic structure for component classification, property assignment, and relationships within the tunnel system hierarchy.
Final closure joint system connecting the last immersed tunnel element to complete structural continuity with integrated waterproofing and load transfer mechanisms.

Integral element forming part of the final immersed tunnel infrastructure designed for operational service life according to GBT 51318-2019 durability requirements. Characterized by design life compatibility with overall tunnel system performance specifications and maintenance protocols.

Electrochemical corrosion protection system utilizing sacrificial metal anodes with specified dimensional characteristics including bearing diameter, heights, spacing, and mounting configurations for marine environment protection.

Structural analysis phase corresponding to specific loading conditions and construction sequences according to GBT 51318-2019 design methodology. Each stage represents distinct structural behavior and loading scenarios throughout the tunnel construction lifecycle.

Structural design criterion defining threshold conditions for structural safety and serviceability verification according to GBT 51318-2019 design principles. Represents boundary conditions beyond which structural performance becomes unacceptable.

Transportation phase where prefabricated tunnel elements are floated on water surface and towed to installation positions as defined in GBT 51318-2019 Section 2.1.3. This stage involves buoyancy control, hydrodynamic loading, and positioning accuracy requirements.
Secondary waterstop system using chloroprene rubber with bolt-and-plate fixation for enhanced joint waterproofing.
Base class for anti-corrosion protection systems.

Stabilization phase following ballasting and backfill operations ensuring structural stability and proper load distribution per GBT 51318-2019 requirements. This stage involves final weight adjustment and foundation settlement monitoring.
Functional element providing safety systems, emergency provisions, and hazard mitigation for tunnel operation according to safety standards and operational requirements.
Anti-corrosion coating with section parameters.

Non-load-bearing element providing specialized operational functionality including environmental protection, system integration, or service delivery within the immersed tunnel infrastructure. Designed according to GBT 51318-2019 functional performance requirements without primary structural load resistance responsibilities.
Concrete shear key component with reinforcement bars and support structures.
Connection steel plate with specifications and positioning.
Designated space or provision reserved for future equipment installation, system expansion, or operational requirements not specified in initial design phase.
General category for scientific publications including journal articles, conference papers, and academic publications contributing to the advancement of immersed tunnel engineering knowledge.
Peer-reviewed scholarly publication presenting research findings, theoretical developments, or case studies in immersed tunnel engineering for scientific community dissemination.
Sacrificial anode bearing component with bearing diameter, height, and spacing specifications per HPDI requirements.
End steel shell component comprising outer panel, end plate, inner panel, and overall shell.
Anti-corrosion system for concrete structures.
Functional element providing water barrier protection and sealing systems for tunnel structures according to GBT 51318-2019 waterproofing standards and marine environment requirements.

Structural capacity verification criterion under maximum design loads ensuring structural integrity and safety per GBT 51318-2019 requirements. Represents conditions associated with structural collapse, overturning, or loss of equilibrium.

Comprehensive technical document defining performance requirements, material properties, dimensional tolerances, and acceptance criteria for tunnel components and systems according to applicable standards.
Anti-corrosion system for steel structures.
Push-out type final joint with multiple sections and connection steel plates.
End plate of steel shell with thickness and height specifications.

Prefabricated tubular structural element constituting primary tunnel enclosure designed according to GBT 51318-2019 element specifications. Characterized by controlled manufacturing tolerances, integrated connection systems, and suitability for floating transportation and underwater installation procedures.
Sacrificial anode leg component with leg height, diameter, and fillet radius specifications per HPDI requirements.
Scholarly documentation of research findings, experimental results, and technical investigations related to immersed tunnel engineering and technology advancement.
Waterstop plate in final joint with final joint length and section parameters.

Construction-phase element utilized during fabrication, transportation, or installation processes according to GBT 51318-2019 construction methodology. Designed for removal or replacement upon completion of specific construction stages without compromising permanent structural integrity.
Sacrificial anode base component with anode height, base height, and base width specifications per HPDI requirements.
General grouting pipe component for waterproofing applications per HPDI requirements.
Intellectual property protection for innovative technologies, methods, or devices related to immersed tunnel engineering and construction.
Technical documentation containing design specifications, calculations, and drawings for immersed tunnel systems according to GBT 51318-2019 design requirements.
Comprehensive scholarly treatise providing detailed analysis and documentation of specific aspects of immersed tunnel technology and engineering practice.

Construction phase involving the manufacturing of tunnel elements in controlled dry dock facilities according to GBT 51318-2019 specifications. This stage encompasses concrete curing, prestressing operations, and quality control processes under factory conditions.

Positioning phase involving temporary restraint and precise alignment of tunnel elements before immersion operations. Critical for ensuring compliance with GBT 51318-2019 placement tolerance requirements and joint alignment specifications.

Structural connection element facilitating continuity between adjacent tunnel segments while providing watertight sealing and load transfer mechanisms. Designed according to GBT 51318-2019 connection requirements with specified deformation compatibility and environmental resistance properties.
Expanded section with length and parameters.

Service phase during the operational lifecycle of the tunnel including service loads and long-term performance according to GBT 51318-2019 design life requirements. This stage encompasses traffic loading, environmental effects, and structural monitoring over the design service period.
Protective element providing corrosion resistance and material degradation prevention for tunnel structures in marine environments according to GBT 51318-2019 durability requirements.
Crimped steel plates for OMEGA system with tube dimensions, chamfer specifications, and baseline distances per HPDI requirements.
Bolts for GINA waterstop system with specifications and spacing per HPDI requirements.
External waterproofing layer system for immersed tunnel elements.
Waterproofing system for construction joints between elements.

Load-bearing structural element designed to provide mechanical resistance and structural integrity within the immersed tunnel system. Characterized by defined load paths, material properties, and capacity for force transmission according to GBT 51318-2019 structural design principles and limit state verification requirements.

Base class for all project outputs, documentation, and deliverable items related to immersed tunnel engineering projects. Encompasses technical documents, research outputs, and intellectual property generated during project lifecycle.
Inner panel of end steel shell with thickness, width, height specifications.
Base class for shear key components with width, height, and length specifications per HPDI requirements.

Waterstop glue with reserved hole size specifications.
